You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for status operations.

STATUS COMMANDS
  status:      Print information about relevant issues, pull requests, and notifications


Note: This command shows status across all your repositories. The --repo flag can be used to filter to a specific repository.

Example usage:
- Check status: GH_PAGER="" gh status
- Check org status: GH_PAGER="" gh status --org <organization>
- Check repo status: GH_PAGER="" gh status --repo <owner/repo> 